<subSubSection id="3FA90BDA257EFFF13C85FA47D8C7F958" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="770C5851257EFFF13C85FA47DDD2FA39" blockId="3.[174,471,1466,1493]" box="[174,471,1466,1493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
<heading id="2C44EF3D257EFFF13C85FA47DDD2FA39" box="[174,471,1466,1493]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="B0B323D2257EFFF13C85FA47DDD2FA39" authority="Page, 1988" authorityName="Page" authorityYear="1988" box="[174,471,1466,1493]" class="Discosea" family="Vannellidae" genus="Vannella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Vannellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="45C78443257EFFF13C85FA47DD56FA38" bold="true" box="[174,339,1466,1493]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">Vannella lata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="132225A0257EFFF13D71FA46DDD2FA39" author="Page, F. C." box="[346,471,1466,1493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref3101" refString="Page, F. C. 1988. A new key to freshwater and soil gymnamoebae. Freshwater Biological Association. Ambleside, Cumbria, UK, 1 - 122." type="book chapter" year="1988">Page, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770C5851257EFFF13CC8FA27D8C7F958" blockId="3.[174,1233,1498,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
The species belongs to the fan-shaped morphotype (fig. 4). The locomotive forms are crescent in shape. The amoeba is wider than long. The hyaline edge elongates when the cell changes the direction of its movement and hugs the cell’s sides. The cytoplasm does not form pseudopodia or subpseudopodia. There are no uroidal structures. The contractile vacuoles are mostly situated near the hyaline edge. The cell’s posterior is conical. The dimensions of the locomotive form are 35–52 µm, the L/B ratio is 0.5–1.5. The single nucleus is 3–5 µm in diameter. The floating form has long sharp radial subpseudopodia (fig. 4, 
<emphasis id="45C78443257EFFF13888F967D8B4F959" box="[1187,1201,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">8</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3FA90BDA257EFFF63CC8F946DEA1FAE6" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="295" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" type="description">
<paragraph id="770C5851257EFFF13CC8F946DEB6F939" blockId="3.[174,1233,1498,1845]" box="[227,691,1722,1749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">We did not observe any cyst formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770C5851257EFFF13CC8F927DDDFF8D8" blockId="3.[174,1233,1498,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
The diagnosis of the species includes a fan-shaped body, the cell’s width is twice its length, the floating form has long sharp pseudopodia whose length exceeds their diameter (
<bibRefCitation id="132225A0257EFFF13C9DF8E7DDCBF8D8" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." box="[182,462,1818,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref3132" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770C58512579FFF63CF0FB6FD8CCFB26" blockId="4.[166,1225,1169,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<taxonomicName id="B0B323D22579FFF63CF0FB6FDD35FB46" authorityName="Page" authorityYear="1988" box="[219,304,1169,1195]" class="Discosea" family="Vannellidae" genus="Vannella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Vannellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="45C784432579FFF63CF0FB6FDD35FB46" box="[219,304,1169,1195]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">V. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the water bodies of Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="132225A02579FFF63F1FFB6CD84EFB41" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." box="[820,1099,1169,1196]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref3132" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). We have previously found 
<taxonomicName id="B0B323D22579FFF63E35FB4FDE6AFB26" authorityName="Page" authorityYear="1988" box="[542,623,1201,1227]" class="Discosea" family="Vannellidae" genus="Vannella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Vannellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="45C784432579FFF63E35FB4FDE6AFB26" box="[542,623,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">V. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the water bodies of 
<collectingRegion id="B57796B32579FFF63FAEFB4CD8CCFB26" box="[901,1225,1201,1227]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Zhytomyr, Volyn and Kyiv</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770C58512579FFF63C8DFB2CD8CCFB06" blockId="4.[166,1225,1169,1292]" box="[166,1225,1233,1260]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
Polissia (
<bibRefCitation id="132225A02579FFF63D3AFB2CDE24FB06" author="Patcyuk, M. K. &amp; Dovgal, I. V." box="[273,545,1233,1259]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="355 - 360" refId="ref3415" refString="Patcyuk, M. K., Dovgal, I. V. 2012. Biotopic distribution of naked amoebes (Protista) in Ukrainian Polissya area. Vestnik Zoologii, 46 (4), 355 - 360." type="journal article" year="2012">Patcyuk, Dovgal, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="132225A02579FFF63E04FB2CDEE8FB01" author="Patsyuk, M. K." box="[559,749,1233,1260]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="98 - 107" refId="ref3630" refString="Patsyuk, M. K. 2014 c. Seasonal Changes in Naked amoebae Species Complex in the River Kamyanka (Zhytomyr City). Journal of Zaporizhzhya National University: collection of scientific works. Biological sciences. Zaporizhzhya National University, Zaporizhzhya, 2, 98 - 107 [In Ukrainian]." type="journal article" year="2014">Patsyuk, 2014 c</bibRefCitation>
). The Dnieper River in the vicinities of
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770C58512579FFF63C8DFB0CDEA1FAE6" blockId="4.[166,1225,1169,1292]" box="[166,676,1265,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<collectingRegion id="B57796B32579FFF63C8DFB0CDD0EFAE6" box="[166,267,1265,1291]" country="Ukraine" name="Kherson" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Kherson</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingRegion id="B57796B32579FFF63D32FB0CDDD8FAE1" box="[281,477,1265,1292]" country="Ukraine" name="Kherson" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Kherson Region</collectingRegion>
) is a new locality
</paragraph>
